<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-83-0598 </DOCNO><TEXT>The early diagnosis of disk space infections and sacroiliitis in childrencan be difficult because of protean presenting symptoms, nonspecificlaboratory studies, and normal plain films. Technetium phosphate scintigraphyhas been reported as a diagnostic method with an accuracy of up to 100%in some series. In this case report we present two patients with negativetechnetium bone scans in the face of active infection, illustrating theneed to pursue the diagnosis using other modalities.</TEXT></DOC>